<subSubSection id="C3776556ED533837FF78F8C0FE58F88B" pageId="514" pageNumber="515" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533837FF78F8C0FE58F88B" blockId="514.[136,778,1601,2070]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED533837FF78F8C0FEFBF8E9" bold="true" box="[189,318,1806,1832]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name refers to the hirsute body of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED533837FF78F89FFBE5F871" pageId="514" pageNumber="515" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533837FF78F89FFC7EFE52" blockId="514.[136,778,1601,2070]" lastBlockId="514.[810,1452,173,1594]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED533837FF78F89FFE07F8AA" bold="true" box="[189,450,1873,1899]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FDE6F89CFD5FF8AD" box="[547,666,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342A</figureCitation>
) swollen, 1.20 mmlong. Prosome 0.91 mmlong; dorsalcephalic shield expanded ventrolaterally, surface densely setulose along ventral border, with paired acutely-pointed posterolateralhorn-likeprocesses (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FDCBF814FD46F835" box="[526,643,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342B</figureCitation>
). Metasome almost spherical, without trace of articulation, slightly longerthanwide. Freeurosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FB53FF63FAC2FF06" box="[1174,1287,173,199]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342C</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented: genital somite much wider than long: 4 abdominal somites setulose on ventral surface, 124×160, 67×127, 44×104, and 58×96 μm, respectively. Caudalramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FAE9FEDDFA66FEEC" box="[1324,1443,275,301]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342D</figureCitation>
) small, setulose, slightly tapering distally, about 2.0 times longer than wide (43×21 μm); caudal setae not discernible from setules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533837FC9AFE55FB3DFCCB" blockId="514.[810,1452,173,1594]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC10FE55FB88FE74" box="[981,1101,411,437]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342E</figureCitation>
) about 1.2 timeslongerthan wide, densely covered with setules, tapering to blunt apex. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC6AFE11FBE5FE38" box="[943,1056,479,505]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342F</figureCitation>
) narrow, 147 μmlong, indistinctly 7-segmented; second to fourth segments each bearing 1 or 2 incomplete subdivisions on posterior surface; armature formula 2, 14, 8, 3+aesthetasc, 1, 4, and 5+aesthetasc. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC5CFDA9FBCAFD40" box="[921,1039,615,641]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342G</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; proximal 3 segments unarmed; terminal segment about 3.4 times longer than wide (57×17 μm) and distinctly longerthan first: armed with 9 setae (arranged as 1, 3, 2, and 3) plus small terminal claw, about 0.3 times as long as segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533837FC9AFCDFFC13FA8A" blockId="514.[810,1452,173,1594]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC10FCDFFB92FCEA" box="[981,1111,785,811]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342H</figureCitation>
) withlarge posteromedian protuberance bearing setules along posterior margin. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC6BFC9BFBE6FCAE" box="[942,1059,853,879]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342J</figureCitation>
) with narrow coxalgnathobase bearing 6 unequalteeth on medial margin: basis with 1 seta onmedial margin: exopodwith 5 setae; outerdistalseta short, about half as long as adjacent seta: endopod with 1 and 6 setae on first and second segments, respectively. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC6FFC31FBD2FBD8" box="[938,1047,1023,1049]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342I</figureCitation>
) armedwith 6 setaeon arthrite, 1 on epipodite, 2 on basis, 4 onexopodand 3 on endopod; setae on endopod longer than those on exopod; arthrite ornamented with patch of setules on proximal medial margin. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FBC2FB49FB4DFB60" box="[1031,1160,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 343" captionStartId="516.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,213,1398]" captionTargetId="figure-19@516.[136,1451,182,1411]" captionTargetPageId="516" captionText="FIGURE 343. Notoixys hirsuta gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591993/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 343A</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented; syncoxa armed with 3, 1, 1, and 1 setae on first to fourth endites, respectively; basiswith 3 setae; first to third endopodal segments with 1, 1, and 3 setae respectively. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FCF7FAC1FC61FAE8" box="[818,932,1295,1321]" captionStart="FIGURE 343" captionStartId="516.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,213,1398]" captionTargetId="figure-19@516.[136,1451,182,1411]" captionTargetPageId="516" captionText="FIGURE 343. Notoixys hirsuta gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591993/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 343B</figureCitation>
) unsegmented, narrowing distally, armed with 3 setae distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533837FC9AFA9AFB54F9F8" blockId="514.[810,1452,173,1594]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
Legs 1–4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC1FFA9DFBFEFAAC" box="[986,1083,1363,1389]" captionStart="FIGURE 343" captionStartId="516.[136,245,1465,1491]" captionTargetBox="[169,1420,213,1398]" captionTargetId="figure-19@516.[136,1451,182,1411]" captionTargetPageId="516" captionText="FIGURE 343. Notoixys hirsuta gen. et sp. nov., female. A, maxilla; B, maxilliped; C, leg 1; D, leg 2; E, leg 3; F, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591993" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591993/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 343</figureCitation>
C-F) biramous; all setae on legs short and naked except pinnate inner coxal seta and outer seta on basis of leg 1. Leg 1 endopod distinctly 2- segmented; but segmentation of other rami of legs 1–4 obscure. Inner coxal seta present only in leg 1. Inner distal seta on basis of leg 1 smooth, 19 μm long. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533837FC9AF8FEFC57F84F" blockId="514.[810,1452,1839,2070]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED533837FC7AF8FEFBFCF88B" box="[959,1081,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 342" captionStartId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-17@515.[208,1380,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="515" captionText="FIGURE 342. Notoixys hirsuta n gen. et sp. nov., female. A. habitus, right; B, cephalic horn; C, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; D, right caudal ramus, dorsal; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, maxillule; J, mandible. Scale bars: A, C, 0.1 mm; B, D, F–J, 0.02 mm; E, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Fig. 342B</figureCitation>
) represented by 2 small setae on posteroventral margin of somite, near base of free urosome.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533837FC9AF858FBE5F871" blockId="514.[810,1452,1839,2070]" box="[863,1056,1942,1968]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED533837FC9AF858FC59F871" bold="true" box="[863,924,1942,1968]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED533831FC9AF876FA8BF88B" lastPageId="516" lastPageNumber="517" pageId="514" pageNumber="515" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED533831FC9AF876FF27F7D7" blockId="514.[810,1452,1839,2070]" lastBlockId="516.[136,779,1601,2070]" lastPageId="516" lastPageNumber="517" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED533837FC9AF876FC09F813" bold="true" box="[863,972,1976,2002]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED533837FC1DF876FB4BF813" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[984,1166,1976,2002]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="514" pageNumber="515" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsuta" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED533837FC1DF876FB4BF813" box="[984,1166,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">Notoixys hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED533837FB56F876FAFEF813" bold="true" box="[1171,1339,1976,2002]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED533837FB56F876FAFEF813" box="[1171,1339,1976,2002]" pageId="514" pageNumber="515" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses a seta-tipped coxal endite on the maxillule and has 3 setae on the third endopodal segment of the maxilla. Within the genus, both features are shared only with the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED553831FD1CF98CFCCCF99D" box="[729,777,1602,1628]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FF23F9AAFEBAF9BC" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[230,383,1635,1662]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heardensis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FF23F9AAFF3CF9BC" box="[230,249,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FEC2F9ADFEBAF9BC" box="[263,383,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">heardensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FE43F9AAFDF6F9BF" bold="true" box="[390,563,1636,1662]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FE43F9AAFDF6F9BF" box="[390,563,1636,1662]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
However, they can be distinguished by the number of setae on the second endopodal segment of the mandible (
<quantity id="4C959B38ED553831FD8BF969FD47F900" box="[590,642,1703,1729]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FD55F966FCCCF900" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[656,777,1703,1730]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsuta" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FD55F966FD61F900" box="[656,676,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FD7FF969FCCCF900" box="[698,777,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FF4DF904FEFBF925" bold="true" box="[136,318,1738,1764]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FF4DF904FEFBF925" box="[136,318,1738,1764]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. etsp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
comparedto 
<quantity id="4C959B38ED553831FE1BF907FDC9F922" box="[478,524,1737,1764]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FDD0F904FD75F922" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[533,688,1737,1764]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heardensis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FDD0F904FDEDF922" box="[533,552,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FDFDF907FD75F922" box="[568,688,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">heardensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FD7FF904FF22F8C7" bold="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FD7FF904FF22F8C7" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). The rami of legs 2–4 are also different: the exopods of legs 3 and 4 are armed with totals of 13 and 12 setae, respectively in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FE66F8FEFDD0F88B" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[419,533,1840,1866]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsuta" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FE66F8FEFE73F888" box="[419,438,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FE03F8FEFDD0F88B" box="[454,533,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FDDBF8FEFD17F88B" bold="true" box="[542,722,1840,1866]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FDDBF8FEFD17F88B" box="[542,722,1840,1866]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and the endopods are armed with 9 and 8 setae, respectively. In contrast, in all three congeners the numbers of these setae are lower, for example, with a maximum of 12 and 11, respectively, on the exopods of legs 3 and 4, and 6 setae on each endopod, as found in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FDDFF814FD76F835" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[538,691,2010,2036]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heardensis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FDDFF814FDE8F832" box="[538,557,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FDFEF814FD76F835" box="[571,691,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">heardensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FD7EF814FF27F7D7" bold="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FD7EF814FF27F7D7" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED523836FF4DF8BDFD24F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591991" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4591991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591991/files/figure.png" pageId="515" pageNumber="516" startId="515.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[241,1353,210,1849]" targetPageId="515">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED523836FF4DF8BDFD24F813" blockId="515.[136,1452,1907,2002]" pageId="515" pageNumber="516">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED523836FF4DF8BDFEEBF84F" bold="true" box="[136,302,1907,1934]" pageId="515" pageNumber="516">FIGURE 342.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED523836FEF0F8BAFE2BF84F" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[309,494,1908,1934]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="515" pageNumber="516" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsuta" status="n gen. et sp. nov.">
