<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FC9AF98CFBDDF99A" box="[863,1048,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">Notoixys hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FBE4F98CFB16F99D" bold="true" box="[1057,1235,1602,1628]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FBE4F98CFB16F99D" box="[1057,1235,1602,1628]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has an inner coxal seta only on leg 1, as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FBFDF9AAFB06F9BC" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1080,1219,1635,1662]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planiceps" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FBFDF9AAFB8FF9BC" box="[1080,1098,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FB9CF9ADFB06F9BC" box="[1113,1219,1635,1661]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">planiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FB0FF9AAFABDF9BF" bold="true" box="[1226,1400,1636,1662]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FB0FF9AAFABDF9BF" box="[1226,1400,1636,1662]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see below). However, unlike the latter species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FAC3F948FAB0F95E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1286,1397,1669,1696]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hirsuta" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FAC3F948FADDF95E" box="[1286,1304,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FAE3F94BFAB0F95E" box="[1318,1397,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">hirsuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FABEF948FC6CF903" bold="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FABEF948FC6CF903" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
possesses more teeth on the medial margin of the mandibular coxal gnathobase, 2 setae (vs. 
<quantity id="4C959B38ED553831FA9EF904FA4CF922" box="[1371,1417,1737,1764]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED553831FA57F904FC51F8C4" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" class="Ascidiacea" family="Didemnidae" genus="Notoixys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planiceps" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FA57F904FA61F922" box="[1426,1444,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FCEFF925FC51F8C4" box="[810,916,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">planiceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFED553831FC5DF922FBFBF8C7" bold="true" box="[920,1086,1772,1798]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED553831FC5DF922FBFBF8C7" box="[920,1086,1772,1798]" pageId="516" pageNumber="517" rank="species">gen. etsp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) onthebasisof themaxillule, and has obscurely segmented rami on the posterior swimming legs, although there are more setae on these rami.
</paragraph>
